Nice! Just a nitpick:
Now this line seems unreachable. See codecov: https://app.codecov.io/gh/JanusGraph/janusgraph/compare/2169/diff

Also sample test code:

```java
    @Test
    public void testPagingIterator() {
        clopen(option(PAGE_SIZE), 10);
        int numVertices = 10;
        for (int i = 0; i < numVertices; i++) {
            graph.addVertex().property("prop", i);
        }
        graph.tx().commit();

        List<Object> values = graph.traversal().V().values("prop").toList();
        assertEquals(numVertices, values.size());
        assertEquals(numVertices, new HashSet<>(values).size());
    }
```

Seems the underlying Datastax driver needs to execute the query once more to know that the current result set is fully fetched. Thus this if-statement seems to be useless.

